# Quality Policy

Openwater maintains a formal Quality Management System (QMS) in compliance with FDA 21 CFR Part 820 and ISO 13485. Our quality policy reflects three core commitments:

**Quality is the responsibility of every individual.** All Openwater employees, contractors, and collaborators share accountability for the quality of our platforms and outputs.

**Compliance with applicable regulatory requirements.** Our QMS ensures that hardware, software, and services meet the standards required by FDA 21 CFR Part 820, ISO 13485, and other applicable regulatory frameworks.

**Continual improvement.** We regularly review measurable quality objectives to evaluate and improve the effectiveness of our Quality Management System.

Community contributions to Openwater platforms are subject to review processes aligned with these commitments. Contributors are encouraged to report defects, unexpected behaviors, and safety-relevant observations through the issue tracking systems maintained in each repository.
